China Internet Valuations Show ‘Inflation,’ Lee Says

-- B y   M a r k   L e e
-- 
2011-04-15T01:12:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/china-internet-valuations-show-inflation-lee-says-correct-.html
(Corrects quotation in headline and first paragraph.)  The valuation of publicly-traded
Chinese Internet companies is showing a “certain degree of
inflation,” Kai-Fu Lee, former president of Google Inc.’s
operations in  China , said in a Bloomberg Television interview
today. Lee said there is no bubble in the sector.  To contact the reporter on this story:
